Introduction:

The project is about literacy and creating a professional online presence as a Student Digital Ambassador. In today’s world it is really important for a person to be digitally literate and able to use digital tools effectively and safely. There are five tasks to be completed for this project covering areas such as digital literacy awareness building a digital portfolio coding platforms, professional online communication and safe practices against cybercrime.
During the project I got to experience a variety of platforms and tools create informative content and understand how to communicate professionally online. I also learned about the significance of safety and digital literacy. This project is designed to ensure that students are digitally literate and able to use digital tools and maintain a strong and professional online presence as a Student Digital Ambassador.

Task1:
For Task 1 of the project, I created a Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic using Prezi. Prezi is a presentation tool that enables users to create appealing and creative content. My infographic presentation focuses on creating awareness about literacy and its significance for students. It covers areas such as digital literacy, digital tools for students and safe internet practices. It also shows how digital literacy is effective in communication, online safety and creating an online presence as a Student Digital Ambassador.
Creating the infographic was interesting as I had to arrange the content in a way that it's visually appealing and easy to comprehend. But it was a little difficult to balance the quantity and the design of content without overloading it. Basically, the task pressed upon me to be more creative and to realise the need of communication of essential information via digital media.

