Task4:
One situation where digital communication led to a problem was when a student sent an email to a professor using language and without a proper subject line. The email was not clear. The request was not properly explained. This situation shows how poor digital communication may lead to problems, including misunderstanding and a lack of professionalism.
To avoid problems it is essential to use a subject line, proper language and a proper message structure. Proper communication practices are important for communication and for building a professional image. Through this task I learned the importance of digital communication as a Student Digital Ambassador.

Task5:
During my research on cybercrime I was most surprised by the fact that people can easily fall victims to crimes by divulging crucial information such as OTP or UPI PIN. This is possible because most scammers employ tactics to lure people into divulging such information. This makes them highly effective in their operations.
I also came to the conclusion that minor slip-ups such as clicking on links or responding to suspicious messages can lead to substantial financial losses. This makes one more aware of the risks involved in the process. So one habit I am going to develop is to be more careful while using platforms. This is going to be helpful for me in the future to remain safe while using platforms as a Student Digital Ambassador.
This project has been highly beneficial as I have gained valuable insights into digital literacy and its importance in the present world. I have also gained knowledge on how to use platforms through the five tasks. I have gained knowledge about the importance of literacy and the various practices to be followed while using digital platforms. This project has helped me develop both communication skills. I have also gained confidence to use platforms in a more professional way as a Student Digital Ambassador. This project has prepared me to be more aware, skilled and professional, in the world.

